## Step 4 — Add Vimeo video to worldVideos map

```tsx
const worldVideos: Record<string, { vimeoId: string; title: string }> = {
  "aqua-azul":       { vimeoId: "1169180228", title: "The Lost City of Aqua Azul" },
  "fossil-frontier": { vimeoId: "1169313594", title: "Fossil Frontier" },
  "my-world-slug":   { vimeoId: "VIMEO_ID",   title: "My World Name" },
};
```

### Vimeo URL params (always use all of these)
```
?badge=0&autopause=0&byline=0&portrait=0&title=0&autoplay=1&loop=1&controls=0
```
- `badge=0` — removes Vimeo watermark
- `byline=0` — removes author name
- `portrait=0` — removes profile picture
- `title=0` — removes video title overlay
- `controls=0` — hides player controls so video fills the frame cleanly
- `autoplay=1` + `loop=1` — plays and loops automatically
- DO NOT use `background=1` or `muted=1` — these force silence
- iframes are always mounted in the DOM (never conditionally rendered) so Vimeo pre-buffers and there is zero delay on hover

---

## Behaviour
- **Idle**: map tint overlay is ON (dark) so 3D globes pop
- **Hover world WITH video**: tint lifts (opacity 0), video fades in behind 3D scene
- **Hover world WITHOUT video**: tint stays ON, globe still reacts (scale + glow ring)
- **Click any island**: detail panel slides up with world info + "Enter this world →" button
- Aqua Azul detail panel shows the illustration image; all others show emoji
